<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08039a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08039a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08039a"> 39(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> glorified boreen</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Move for Better Roads / Offaly&apos;s &ldquo;Glorified Boreens&rdquo;</b> Some hard hits at inefficient administration and bad roads were made at a Tullamore meeting, which formed an association for the improvement of the roads.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Mr. Goodbody, solr., declared the highways in Offaly were not roads at all, but &ldquo;<mark>glorified boreens</mark>.&rdquo; <small> <a name="II13feb23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#II13feb23"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (13 February 1923) 8/3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Anglo-Irish <i>boreen</i>: a lane, a narrow road. </mm> </dd></dl>
